NEW YORK, United States of America, May 30, 2018/APO Group/ -- 
                                                
                        The Secretary-General condemns the attack that killed two police officers and a civilian in Liege, Belgium, on Tuesday. He extends his condolences to the families of the victims, the people and the Government of Belgium and wishes those injured a speedy recovery.





The United Nations stands in solidarity with Belgium in its fight against terrorism and violent extremism.